title: Grateful Dead Live at Laguna Seca Recreation Area on 1987-05-09
description:
Set 1

Sugar Magnolia-> Sugaree, Me & My Uncle-> Mexicali Blues, When Push Comes To Shove, Tons Of Steel, My Brother Esau, Tennessee Jed, Let It Grow

Set 2

Touch Of Grey, Looks Like Rain, He's Gone-> Drums-> Space-> The Wheel-> The Other One-> Wharf Rat-> Around & Around-> Sunshine Daydream, E: Iko Iko

Ry Cooder then Bruce Hornsby & the Range Opened; during Tons of Steel, Brent sings "I can only hope my bass-player will cut me a little slack"!!

reviews.review_text: Speed issue Listened to first three tracks only.  Slower than they should be .  Dying batteries?

- Great listening experience. Unusually organized setlist, & the band are obviously enjoying the playfulness of that. Maybe not spectacular, but the feel of it is very warm, & I really love shows that would make good introductions for people who've never been to a show to see what it could be like. This is one of those!
